## B. 3 Proof of Equivalence for Transformed Data

Proof. From

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \tilde{\mathbf{X}}=(\mathbf{I}+(\sqrt{\gamma}-1) \Pi_{\mathbf{A}}) \mathbf{X} \\
& \tilde{\mathbf{Y}}=(\mathbf{I}+(\sqrt{\gamma}-1) \Pi_{\mathbf{A}}) \mathbf{Y}
\end{aligned}
$$

we can easily derive that

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{S}_{\tilde{X} \tilde{Y}} & =\frac{1}{n-1}(\tilde{\mathbf{X}} \tilde{\mathbf{Y}})^{T}(\tilde{\mathbf{X}} \tilde{\mathbf{Y}}) \\
& =\frac{1}{n-1}\left((\mathbf{X Y}+(\sqrt{\gamma}-1) \Pi_{\mathbf{A}} \mathbf{X Y})^{T}(\mathbf{X Y}+(\sqrt{\gamma}-1) \Pi_{\mathbf{A}} \mathbf{X Y})\right)
\end{aligned}
$$

As $\Pi_{\mathbf{A}}$ is an orthogonal projection, we have that $(\mathbf{X Y})^{T}\left(\Pi_{\mathbf{A}} \mathbf{X Y}\right)=\Pi_{\mathbf{A}}(\mathbf{X Y})^{T} \mathbf{X Y}=\mathbf{S}_{X Y \mid A}$, leading to

$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathbf{S}_{\tilde{X} \tilde{Y}} & =\mathbf{S}_{X Y}+2(\sqrt{\gamma}-1) \mathbf{S}_{X Y \mid A}+(\sqrt{\gamma}-1)^{2} \mathbf{S}_{X Y \mid A} \\
& =\mathbf{S}_{X Y}+(\gamma-1) \mathbf{S}_{X Y \mid A}
\end{aligned}
$$

Thus, by linearity of $f_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}}$, the minimiser of $f_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}}\left(\mathbf{S}_{\tilde{X} \tilde{Y}}\right)$ is given by

$$
\begin{aligned}
\boldsymbol{\Theta}^{\gamma} & =\operatorname{argmin}_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}} f_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}}\left(\mathbf{S}_{\tilde{X} \tilde{Y}}\right) \\
& =\operatorname{argmin}_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}} f_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}}\left(\mathbf{S}_{X Y}\right)+(\gamma-1) f_{\boldsymbol{\Theta}}\left(\mathbf{S}_{X Y \mid A}\right)
\end{aligned}
$$

This conclude the proof.
